import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt


def plot(A):
    U, S, V = np.linalg.svd(A)
    v = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, 100) 
    x = np.cos(v)
    y = np.sin(v)
    x1 = (A[0][0] * x + A[0][1] * y)
    y1 = (A[1][0] * x + A[1][1] * y)
    
    v1 = V.T[0] 
    v2 = V.T[1]

    u1 = U[:,0][:2] 
    u2 = U[:,1][:2]
    
    origin = np.array([[0, 0],[0, 0]]) 
    
    fig= plt.figure(figsize=(5,5))
    p1 = plt.gca()
    plt.title('Right')
    p1.plot(x, y)
    p1.quiver(*origin,[v1[0], v2[0]],[v1[1],v2[1]],scale_units='xy',scale=1)

    fig= plt.figure(figsize=(5,5))
    p2 = plt.gca()
    plt.title('Left')
    p2.plot(x1, y1)
    k = np.array([S[0]*u1, S[1]*u2])
    print(k)
    p2.quiver(*origin, k[:,0], k[:,1] ,scale_units='xy', scale = 1)


    plt.show()

p = 5000
k = 100
A = np.diag(np.diag(np.random.rand(p, p)))
U = np.random.rand(p, k)
V = np.random.rand(k, p)

def woodbury(A, U, V):  # по формуле с расчетом обратной матрицы через функцию inv
    A_inv = np.linalg.inv(A)
    return A_inv - A_inv @ U @ np.linalg.inv(np.eye(k, dtype=float) + V @ A_inv @ U) @ V @ A_inv

def woodbury_diag(A, U, V):   # с подсчетом обратной матрицы вручную
    A_inv = A
    for i in range(p):
        A_inv[i][i] = 1/ A_inv[i][i]
    return A_inv - A_inv@ U @ np.linalg.inv(np.eye(k, dtype=float) + V@A_inv@U)@V@A_inv
